are the syptoms for cancer always lost of weight or fever no in the majority of cancer there are no significant symptoms until the disease is very advanced even with advanced disease cancer symptoms can mimic other physical conditions once the cancer is advanced a few of the symptoms to be suspicious about includes swollen lymph nodes any cancer can cause this not just lymphoma fluid retention in the belly legs feet feeling hungry but not being able to eat general feeling of unease but the most important symptom is either noticing or feeling an unexplained lump or bump anywhere on the body if the lump or bump seems to be growing have it checked immediately my sons most obvious symptom was not loss of weight but the fact that he was gaining weight even though he was not eating come to find out fluid retention and tumor burden the weight of the tumors had increased his belly by pounds Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Stomach cancer Prostate cancer Colorectal cancer Hodgkin's lymphoma Breast cancer Ovarian cancer Lung cancer Cancer of the larynx Diarrhea Esophageal cancer Mesothelioma Brain tumor Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Soft tissue sarcoma Coeliac disease Malignant melanoma Folic acid Radiation therapy Testicular cancer Renal cell carcinoma Multiple myeloma Aspartame Group A streptococcal infection Chronic fatigue syndrome Hypoglycemia Tobacco smoking Metastasis Acute lymphoblastic leukemia Muscle Multiple sclerosis Traumatic brain injury Weight loss Bone marrow transplant Stroke Thyroid cancer Hypertension Diabetes mellitus Chronic lymphocytic leukemia Hyperthermia Anorexia nervosa AIDS Lymphedema Cervical cancer Obesity Alcoholism Infectious mononucleosis Lupus erythematosus Lymphatic system Oncology Breast Glaucoma Tuberculosis Clinical depression Growth hormone treatment Wilms' tumor Osteoarthritis Dehydration Cirrhosis Atkins Nutritional Approach Crohn's disease Pancreatic cancer Physical examination Pneumonia Eczema Medicine Doxepin Immune system Tumor Endometr